place.name: FRENZE
place.gazetteerText: FRENZE, a parish in Depwade district, Norfolk; on the S border of the county, and on an affluent of the river Waveney, near Diss r. station, 1½ mile E by N of Diss. Post town, Scole. Acres, 399. Real property, £600. Pop., 49. Houses, 11. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £7 0. Patron, S. Smith, Esq. The church has eight brasses of the Blenhaysetts; and is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
